In settings, under appearance, under background set to 'Transparent background' and set Opacity to 0.55
For full screen do the following:
    - Right click and check 'Fullscreen'
For removing the menubar, do one of the following:
    - Right click and uncheck menubar (note: this will need to be done every time you open a terminal
In settings, under appearance, under background set to 'Transparent background' and set Opacity to 0.55
For full screen do the following:
    - Right click and check 'Fullscreen'
For removing the menubar, do one of the following:
    - Right click and uncheck menubar (note: this will need to be done every time you open a terminal
In settings, under appearance, under background set to 'Transparent background' and set Opacity to 0.55
For full screen do the following:
    - Right click and check 'Fullscreen'
For removing the menubar, do one of the following:
    - Right click and uncheck menubar (note: this will need to be done every time you open a terminal
    - Go into settings, under appearance, under 'Opening New Windows' and uncheck 'Display menubar in new windows'
